00:59:09,083 --> 00:59:11,416
Even then you didn't starve.

963
00:59:11,542 --> 00:59:15,035
There's always been somebody
to take care of our Joe.

964
00:59:16,750 --> 00:59:18,582
Got extra.

965
00:59:18,708 --> 00:59:20,620
You told me yourself.

966
00:59:20,750 --> 00:59:23,367
Because you got along so well
with the guards.

967
00:59:29,500 --> 00:59:32,334
Why didn't you have the guts to escape?

968
00:59:33,125 --> 00:59:34,912
Like Jack Wales.

969
00:59:37,542 --> 00:59:40,330
Don't mention that swine's name to me.

970
00:59:41,125 --> 00:59:43,492
It was all right for him to escape.

971
00:59:43,625 --> 00:59:47,073
He had a rich father to look after him
and buy him an education.

972
00:59:48,042 --> 00:59:51,285
Those three years were
the only chance I'd get to be qualified.

973
00:59:51,417 --> 00:59:54,785
Let those rich bastards
who have all the fun be heroes.

974
00:59:54,917 --> 00:59:56,374
Let them pay for their privileges.

975
00:59:56,500 --> 00:59:58,617
If you want it straight
from the soldier,

976
00:59:58,750 --> 01:00:01,208
I was bloody well pleased
when I was captured.

977
01:00:01,333 --> 01:00:02,869
I didn't like being a prisoner,

978
01:00:03,000 --> 01:00:05,333
but it was a damn sight better
than being dead.

979
01:00:06,500 --> 01:00:08,708
Come to that,

980
01:00:08,833 --> 01:00:12,952
what did you do 50 years ago
back in the Great War?

981
01:00:27,417 --> 01:00:29,409
You want some tea?

982
01:00:31,333 --> 01:00:33,199
I don't want anything.

983
01:00:54,500 --> 01:00:56,492
It was good while it lasted.

984
01:00:57,833 --> 01:00:59,415
I mean that.

985
01:01:05,333 --> 01:01:07,495
I'm sorry it had to end like this.

986
01:01:09,792 --> 01:01:11,249
I'm sorry, too.

987
01:01:13,667 --> 01:01:16,000
Goodbye, Alice.

988
01:01:16,125 --> 01:01:17,866
Goodbye.

989
01:01:56,708 --> 01:01:59,325
- Ah, Cinderella's arrived.
- Hello, Charles.

990
01:02:04,958 --> 01:02:06,995
Yes, he's impossible!

991
01:02:07,125 --> 01:02:09,708
He's always interfering.
Always interfering.

992
01:02:09,833 --> 01:02:12,041
- Whisky, please.
- Yeah, whisky for the gentleman.

993
01:02:12,167 --> 01:02:15,456
Oh, here, that reminds me,
did you hear about the chap

994
01:02:15,583 --> 01:02:17,825
who asked a girl
if she wanted a whisky and sofa?

995
01:02:19,083 --> 01:02:20,745
She said, "I don't want one of them,

996
01:02:20,875 --> 01:02:22,207
"but I'll have a gi...

997
01:02:24,125 --> 01:02:26,037
"I'll have a gin and platonic."

998
01:02:27,833 --> 01:02:30,792
Whisky and sofa, gin and platonic!

999
01:02:30,917 --> 01:02:32,829
It's a play on words.

1000
01:02:32,958 --> 01:02:34,449
Oh, well, you don't understand it.

1001
01:02:34,583 --> 01:02:36,324
Ooh, I wet you there.
Sorry about that.

1002
01:02:36,458 --> 01:02:38,450
Harry, have you heard this one?

1003
01:02:39,208 --> 01:02:41,416
This chap and this girl,
and he says...

1004
01:02:41,542 --> 01:02:43,249
Whisky and sofa!

1005
01:02:47,750 --> 01:02:50,083
"I don't want
a whisky and sofa."

1006
01:02:51,000 --> 01:02:54,164
So, she said,
"I'd like a gin and platonic."

1007
01:02:57,417 --> 01:02:59,079
Good evening, Susan.

1008
01:02:59,208 --> 01:03:00,949
I hope you had a nice holiday.

1009
01:03:01,083 --> 01:03:02,665
Hello, Joe.

1010
01:03:02,792 --> 01:03:04,875
Have you met my father and mother?

1011
01:03:05,000 --> 01:03:07,538
- This is Mr Lampton, Mother.
- How do you do, Mr Lampton?

1012
01:03:07,667 --> 01:03:09,329
I've seen you at the town hall, lad.

1013
01:03:09,458 --> 01:03:11,996
You know His Worship the Mayor,
the Mayoress?

1014
01:03:12,125 --> 01:03:14,742
One of our bright young men
in the Treasurer's Office.

1015
01:03:14,875 --> 01:03:16,082
Well, what are you drinking?

1016
01:03:16,208 --> 01:03:17,870
- Scotch, please.
- Make it a large one.

1017
01:03:18,000 --> 01:03:20,492
- By the way, weren't you at Mildenhall?
- Yes, 551 Squadron.

1018
01:03:20,625 --> 01:03:23,585
- I had a good friend in that squadron.
- I remember the Steppes all right.

1019
01:03:23,708 --> 01:03:25,745
My trouble is
to know when to take 'em!

1020
01:03:25,875 --> 01:03:27,662
Well, give me the Lancers every time.

1021
01:03:27,792 --> 01:03:29,033
Darrow. Chick Darrow.

1022
01:03:29,167 --> 01:03:31,500
He was a nice chap.
I went to school with him.

1023
01:03:31,625 --> 01:03:33,207
No, I don't remember him.

1024
01:03:33,333 --> 01:03:37,156
But you must remember Chick!
Old Chick, why, you couldn't miss him.

1025
01:03:37,292 --> 01:03:38,874
No, no, I've never met him.

1026
01:03:39,750 --> 01:03:41,286
You come from Dufdon, don't you?

1027
01:03:41,417 --> 01:03:43,283
- It was Dufdon, wasn't it?
- Yes, sir.

1028
01:03:43,417 --> 01:03:46,205
Yes. Must be quite a change for you.

1029
01:03:46,333 --> 01:03:47,869
How's Cannon Jones?

1030
01:03:48,000 --> 01:03:51,664
I haven't seen him in...
oh, must be nearly two years.

1031
01:03:51,792 --> 01:03:53,624
Oh, you'll know Cannon Jones,
won't you?

1032
01:03:53,750 --> 01:03:55,662
Leddersford.

1033
01:03:55,792 --> 01:03:57,408
No, I'm afraid, I don't.

1034
01:03:57,542 --> 01:04:00,740
Charming wife and terribly like
Lucy Saunders, don't you think?

1035
01:04:01,375 --> 01:04:03,958
You'll know J.C. Brotherton,
I'm sure of that.

1036
01:04:04,083 --> 01:04:07,326
I know him in much in the same way
as I know the Prime Minister.

1037
01:04:08,625 --> 01:04:11,117
My father used to work in one of his mills
as an overlooker.

1038
01:04:13,333 --> 01:04:15,165
Now, that's nice, don't you think?

1039
01:04:15,292 --> 01:04:17,534
I've noticed with this orchestra,
year after year,

1040
01:04:17,667 --> 01:04:20,250
the older the piece,
the happier they are with it.

1041
01:04:20,375 --> 01:04:23,914
Well, speaking of Dufdon,
extraordinary chap, that Clevely.

1042
01:04:24,042 --> 01:04:27,456
Chucking his money around all right.
He's well on his way to his knighthood.

1043
01:04:27,583 --> 01:04:30,223
He drove Father to a meeting last month.
He's got a large Mercedes.

1044
01:04:30,292 --> 01:04:33,364
Father said he drove like a maniac.
You know him, don't you?

1045
01:04:34,000 --> 01:04:35,491
I don't know any tallymen.

1046
01:04:36,000 --> 01:04:37,957
- Oh, come now.
- I don't follow you, old man.

1047
01:04:38,625 --> 01:04:39,911
A tallyman is...

1048
01:04:40,042 --> 01:04:41,624
Well, he sells clothes on credit,

1049
01:04:41,750 --> 01:04:43,787
money-lending
at fantastic high interest rates.

1050
01:04:44,250 --> 01:04:46,537
It's business.
You wouldn't refuse the profits.

1051
01:04:48,083 --> 01:04:50,245
It's dirty business.

1052
01:04:50,375 --> 01:04:53,823
Henry, I don't know if you're aware of it
or not, but this is our dance.

1053
01:04:53,958 --> 01:04:55,244
Good night, Mr Lampton.

1054
01:04:55,375 --> 01:04:58,288
- Elsie, are you gonna risk it with me?
- Yes, of course.

1055
01:04:58,417 --> 01:04:59,498
Come on, Sue.

1056
01:05:00,583 --> 01:05:02,415
See you later, Sergeant.

1057
01:05:06,500 --> 01:05:09,288
Don't worry about the way
the world's run, lad.

1058
01:05:09,417 --> 01:05:11,875
Enjoy it while you're young.

1059
01:05:14,125 --> 01:05:15,206
Hmm.

1060
01:05:20,250 --> 01:05:21,661
Joe...

1061
01:05:21,792 --> 01:05:24,660
If you're free, I could see you
the dance after next.

1062
01:05:34,167 --> 01:05:37,535
Joe, why didn't you write?

1063
01:05:37,667 --> 01:05:40,375
You didn't write either,
only postcards.

1064
01:05:40,500 --> 01:05:42,116
I was waiting for you to write.

1065
01:05:43,042 --> 01:05:44,658
A girl can't write first.

1066
01:05:45,833 --> 01:05:47,825
Well, she can't
if she has any pride.

1067
01:05:51,375 --> 01:05:53,412
Why did you go away
without letting me know?

1068
01:05:53,542 --> 01:05:55,784
I had to. They sent me away.

1069
01:05:56,708 --> 01:05:59,872
- Don't you believe me?
- Oh, I believe you.

1070
01:06:00,000 --> 01:06:02,083
But that's why I didn't write.

1071
01:06:04,458 --> 01:06:06,290
Because I knew how hopeless it was.

1072
01:06:06,917 --> 01:06:09,330
- Why?
- You know it's hopeless, Susan.

1073
01:06:09,458 --> 01:06:10,539
Tell me, Joe. Please.

1074
01:06:10,667 --> 01:06:12,499
You saw them in there
when I met your parents,

1075
01:06:12,625 --> 01:06:15,368
the way they were needling me,
and you couldn't do anything about it.

1076
01:06:15,500 --> 01:06:18,334
- I wanted to, really I did.
- One day they'll say,

1077
01:06:18,458 --> 01:06:21,121
"You mustn't see
that vulgar person again."

1078
01:06:21,250 --> 01:06:22,912
They wouldn't dare.

1079
01:06:23,833 --> 01:06:26,166
I won't ever let them come between us.

1080
01:06:29,375 --> 01:06:30,957
It's useless, Susan.

1081
01:06:32,208 --> 01:06:33,415
You know it is.

1082
01:06:37,125 --> 01:06:38,741
Let me kiss you.

1083
01:06:41,292 --> 01:06:42,874
Just this once.

1084
01:06:53,458 --> 01:06:55,370
Don't you care about me?

1085
01:06:58,292 --> 01:07:02,616
Maybe... it's because I care too much.

1086
01:07:11,667 --> 01:07:13,750
I love you, Joe.

1087
01:07:14,917 --> 01:07:16,749
I love you.

1088
01:07:16,875 --> 01:07:18,741
I love you, too.

1089
01:07:19,958 --> 01:07:21,665
Do you really?

1090
01:07:23,167 --> 01:07:25,250
Oh, Joe, how much?

1091
01:07:27,458 --> 01:07:29,120
Very much.

1092
01:07:46,792 --> 01:07:48,624
No!

1093
01:07:52,458 --> 01:07:54,199
I'm sorry, Joe.

1094
01:07:54,333 --> 01:07:56,165
Really I am.

1095
01:08:02,750 --> 01:08:04,207
Gosh, I'm hot!

1096
01:08:04,333 --> 01:08:06,450
You shouldn't feel hot.

1097
01:08:06,583 --> 01:08:08,199
You've nothing on.

1098
01:08:09,125 --> 01:08:12,038
Is that better?
Is that what prim Joe wants?

1099
01:08:12,167 --> 01:08:14,124
No, that's not what Joe wants.

1100
01:08:15,333 --> 01:08:17,871
You know what Joe wants.

1101
01:08:18,000 --> 01:08:20,208
It's what all the Joes want.

1102
01:08:21,625 --> 01:08:22,832
Oh, Joe.

1103
01:08:24,125 --> 01:08:28,495
You know, sometimes when you kiss me,
I feel as if you weren't really there.

1104
01:08:28,625 --> 01:08:31,038
I'm here all right, and I can prove it.

1105
01:08:31,167 --> 01:08:34,285
Seriously, Joe,
there's something wrong, isn't there?

1106
01:08:34,417 --> 01:08:38,161
- Don't you like the way I make love?
- Oh, I like it very much.

1107
01:08:38,292 --> 01:08:40,249
It reminds me of a good set
of mixed tennis.

1108
01:08:40,375 --> 01:08:43,101
- That's not a very kind thing to say.
- I sometimes don't feel very kind.

1109
01:08:43,125 --> 01:08:45,242
- Why?
- Well, your mother and father,

1110
01:08:45,375 --> 01:08:47,367
were they kind to me the other night?

1111
01:08:48,625 --> 01:08:50,617
I can just see your mother now,

1112
01:08:50,750 --> 01:08:53,709
saying, "You mustn't see
that vulgar Lampton boy again,

1113
01:08:53,833 --> 01:08:56,667
"the one with the bulging shirt
and the chromium cufflinks."

1114
01:08:57,500 --> 01:09:00,914
Then there's you. You lead me on so far
and then you stop me.

1115
01:09:02,292 --> 01:09:04,158
What do you think I'm made of?

1116
01:09:04,292 --> 01:09:06,705
It's not that I don't want to.

1117
01:09:06,833 --> 01:09:07,949
It's just...

1118
01:09:08,083 --> 01:09:10,416
well, I suppose I'm scared.

1119
01:09:11,375 --> 01:09:15,745
I do love you, Joe, I do!
I'd do anything for you, Joe, anything!

1120
01:09:19,250 --> 01:09:22,368
Except what any girl would do
for the man she loves.

1121
01:09:23,917 --> 01:09:26,660
Joe, how much do you love me?

1122
01:09:27,583 --> 01:09:28,664
Very much.

1123
01:09:30,375 --> 01:09:32,708
About a million pounds' worth.

1124
01:09:36,333 --> 01:09:39,041
Joe, be gentle with me.

1125
01:09:41,750 --> 01:09:44,868
âª Out in the pale moonlight

1126
01:09:45,000 --> 01:09:46,957
âª It wasn't your pa

1127
01:09:47,083 --> 01:09:48,324
âª It wasn't... âª

1128
01:09:49,417 --> 01:09:53,491
Oh, let's face it, darling,
he was a brute, a coarse brute!

1129
01:09:54,333 --> 01:09:56,575
Oh, I know it's hell right this minute,

1130
01:09:56,708 --> 01:09:59,997
but the way I look at it,
he's the loser.

1131
01:10:21,625 --> 01:10:24,333
Come on, Susan.
I think we'd better be going now.

1132
01:10:25,917 --> 01:10:27,624
I don't want to go.

1133
01:10:28,625 --> 01:10:30,833
I don't ever want to go.

1134
01:10:33,375 --> 01:10:35,458
Isn't it super, Joe?

1135
01:10:35,583 --> 01:10:37,575
Now we really belong to each other.

1136
01:10:37,708 --> 01:10:40,826
Really and truly, till death do us part.

1137
01:10:42,750 --> 01:10:44,582
Wasn't it wonderful?

1138
01:10:45,458 --> 01:10:49,031
Wasn't it absolutely
the most wonderful thing

1139
01:10:49,167 --> 01:10:50,783
that ever happened to you?

1140
01:10:54,042 --> 01:10:56,500
- Wasn't it, Joe?
- Yes.

1141
01:10:57,917 --> 01:10:59,658
Come on, let's go.

1142
01:10:59,792 --> 01:11:01,875
Oh, must we really go?

1143
01:11:02,000 --> 01:11:05,038
You know we must.
Besides, your mother...

1144
01:11:05,167 --> 01:11:07,250
Poor Mummy, if only she knew.

1145
01:11:08,042 --> 01:11:09,533
That's quite a thought.

1146
01:11:12,292 --> 01:11:15,831
Joe, do you know
I don't really feel any different?

1147
01:11:15,958 --> 01:11:19,030
I thought I'd feel terribly different
and I don't.

1148
01:11:19,167 --> 01:11:21,409
Joe, do you feel different?

1149
01:11:23,083 --> 01:11:25,666
You don't really want
to talk about it, do you?

1150
01:11:25,792 --> 01:11:28,079
You're not very sentimental, are you?

1151
01:11:28,208 --> 01:11:30,825
No, I'd rather not talk about it.

1152
01:11:30,958 --> 01:11:34,326
Joe, do you know something?
I do believe you're a prig.

1153
01:11:34,458 --> 01:11:37,292
You're really shier than I am, aren't you?
Aren't you really?

1154
01:11:38,333 --> 01:11:40,074
I expect I am.

1155
01:11:41,875 --> 01:11:43,366
Do I look different?

1156
01:11:44,375 --> 01:11:46,662
- Do I, Joe?
- No.

1157
01:11:46,792 --> 01:11:50,991
I don't feel different.
I feel just the same, only better.

1158
01:11:52,292 --> 01:11:54,659
I thought I'd feel so terribly different.

1159
01:11:55,667 --> 01:11:57,249
It's funny.

1160
01:11:57,375 --> 01:11:59,867
Are you sure
I don't look different, Joe?

1161
01:12:00,000 --> 01:12:02,458
Just the tiniest bit? Really sure?

1162
01:12:08,792 --> 01:12:11,409
Hey! Come on, Joe,
what are you waiting for?

1163
01:12:11,542 --> 01:12:14,159
I think I'll hang on for a bit.
I've got some work to do.

1164
01:12:14,292 --> 01:12:16,252
- But it's Friday!
- You can get along without me.

1165
01:12:16,333 --> 01:12:18,559
The last few days
you've been lower than a snake's belly.

1166
01:12:18,583 --> 01:12:19,783
- What's the matter?
- Nothing.

1167
01:12:19,875 --> 01:12:22,768
You ought to be sitting pretty. You said
Susan was your tenner on the pools.

1168
01:12:22,792 --> 01:12:25,309
Well, you're home, lad. You won
first dividend or near as damn it.

1169
01:12:25,333 --> 01:12:27,325
- Everything's going my way.
- Ready, chaps?

1170
01:12:27,458 --> 01:12:29,290
You go ahead.
I don't think I'll come tonight.

1171
01:12:29,417 --> 01:12:31,079
What's the matter with him?
What's wrong?

1172
01:12:31,208 --> 01:12:33,688
Nothing's the matter.
I just don't happen to feel like boozing.

1173
01:12:33,792 --> 01:12:35,499
Come along, Teddy.

1174
01:12:35,625 --> 01:12:37,867
Call in later, Joe, if you feel like it.

1175
01:13:09,333 --> 01:13:10,949
Nothing has changed.

1176
01:13:14,583 --> 01:13:15,994
Nothing at all.

1177
01:13:26,750 --> 01:13:29,333
Oh, I don't care about them.

1178
01:13:29,458 --> 01:13:31,495
I don't either.

1179
01:13:36,792 --> 01:13:38,533
I couldn't do without you.

1180
01:13:39,417 --> 01:13:41,033
I love you, Alice.

1181
01:13:43,125 --> 01:13:44,332
I love you.

1182
01:13:45,375 --> 01:13:46,991
Remember...

1183
01:13:47,125 --> 01:13:49,162
What was it you once said?

1184
01:13:49,292 --> 01:13:50,999
"Loving friends", you said.

1185
01:13:51,917 --> 01:13:53,704
"Let's be loving friends."

1186
01:13:55,917 --> 01:13:58,660
I didn't want to fall in love with you.

1187
01:13:58,792 --> 01:14:01,250
I tried to fall in love with Susan.

1188
01:14:04,667 --> 01:14:06,875
What are we gonna do?

1189
01:14:07,000 --> 01:14:08,457
I don't know.

1190
01:14:09,667 --> 01:14:11,909
It's been hell these last weeks.

1191
01:14:12,917 --> 01:14:14,579
I want you all the time.

1192
01:14:15,458 --> 01:14:17,745
Not just stolen meetings.

1193
01:14:19,250 --> 01:14:22,243
Oh, Alice.
Listen, couldn't we...?

1194
01:14:22,375 --> 01:14:26,039
Well, I have a fortnight
starting next month on the 15th.

1195
01:14:26,167 --> 01:14:29,001
Charles says he knows of a cottage,
belongs to a friend of his.

1196
01:14:30,458 --> 01:14:33,121
We could have it for a few days
for next to nothing.

1197
01:14:34,167 --> 01:14:36,625
And there'd be nobody
for miles around.

1198
01:14:39,458 --> 01:14:41,415
Just us.

1199
01:14:41,542 --> 01:14:43,158
Together.

1200
01:14:44,208 --> 01:14:46,165
Oh, Alice, couldn't we?

1201
01:15:14,167 --> 01:15:15,167
No!

1202
01:15:16,167 --> 01:15:18,329
I've never done this before.

1203
01:15:18,458 --> 01:15:20,700
The next time I do it,

1204
01:15:20,833 --> 01:15:23,416
I tell you, woman,
it's going to be legitimate.

1205
01:15:25,333 --> 01:15:26,995
Darling, you sound like a lawyer.

1206
01:15:27,125 --> 01:15:29,287
I feel more like a Billingsgate porter.

1207
01:15:29,417 --> 01:15:30,578
Hmm!

1208
01:15:30,708 --> 01:15:32,165
Not very flattering.

1209
01:15:44,375 --> 01:15:46,537
Oh, it's nice here.

1210
01:15:55,208 --> 01:15:56,244
There.

1211
01:15:57,208 --> 01:15:58,324
Thank you.

1212
01:16:01,542 --> 01:16:04,125
- You know something?
- Hmm?

1213
01:16:06,333 --> 01:16:08,165
I feel quite shy suddenly.

1214
01:16:09,458 --> 01:16:11,916
As if I really were a young bride.

1215
01:16:12,042 --> 01:16:14,034
I feel rather shy myself.

1216
01:16:15,625 --> 01:16:17,958
Oh, but it's a good feeling.

1217
01:16:18,083 --> 01:16:19,199
Yes.

1218
01:16:25,083 --> 01:16:26,199
No.

1219
01:16:27,167 --> 01:16:30,456
No, I don't want to smoke
and I don't want to drink.

1220
01:16:30,583 --> 01:16:34,076
Because cigarettes and drink,
they dull you.

1221
01:16:35,250 --> 01:16:38,163
I want every minute of these four days.

1222
01:16:38,292 --> 01:16:41,535
And I want them sharp and clear.

1223
01:16:49,250 --> 01:16:50,366
Alice?

1224
01:16:52,542 --> 01:16:55,034
You and George, do you still...?

1225
01:16:57,167 --> 01:16:59,409
Tell me, I want to know. Do you?

1226
01:17:00,875 --> 01:17:04,198
Very well.
The answer is yes, sometimes.

1227
01:17:06,917 --> 01:17:07,953
But...

1228
01:17:08,833 --> 01:17:10,620
Joe...

1229
01:17:10,750 --> 01:17:13,333
You don't know about these things.

1230
01:17:13,458 --> 01:17:17,156
They are not as simple as that.
It's all mixed up.

1231
01:17:17,292 --> 01:17:19,579
- You don't love him.
- No.

1232
01:17:23,000 --> 01:17:24,741
You and him, it's...

1233
01:17:24,875 --> 01:17:26,832
Well, it's not like us, is it?

1234
01:17:26,958 --> 01:17:28,165
No, it's not.

1235
01:17:34,167 --> 01:17:35,908
You're such a honest person.

1236
01:17:37,042 --> 01:17:39,329
Why the hell do you have
to be so honest?

1237
01:17:52,333 --> 01:17:54,950
Darling, I'm glad you're so honest.

1238
01:17:55,083 --> 01:17:56,995
I love you for it.

1239
01:18:19,250 --> 01:18:21,082
Do you have to go tomorrow?

1240
01:18:22,083 --> 01:18:23,494
You know I have.

1241
01:18:27,292 --> 01:18:28,578
You know...

1242
01:18:29,875 --> 01:18:32,834
I used to think it was
a lot of romantic nonsense,

1243
01:18:32,958 --> 01:18:35,166
one man, one woman.

1244
01:18:36,375 --> 01:18:37,991
Not long ago I'd have said...

1245
01:18:39,542 --> 01:18:42,535
...a man could be happy
with any one of a hundred women.

1246
01:18:46,375 --> 01:18:48,958
Now I know you're my woman, Alice.

1247
01:18:49,083 --> 01:18:52,622
My rush. All the love
I'll ever get now or evermore.

1248
01:18:53,792 --> 01:18:56,626
And you've got all the love
I'll ever have to give.

1249
01:19:01,208 --> 01:19:04,167
You've changed so much, Joe.
You know that?

1250
01:19:04,292 --> 01:19:05,499
So have you.

1251
01:19:05,625 --> 01:19:08,618
Yes, I've no more defences.

1252
01:19:09,708 --> 01:19:11,665
How have I changed?

1253
01:19:12,542 --> 01:19:14,158
Oh, I don't know how to say it.

1254
01:19:15,875 --> 01:19:18,538
You're... You're stronger now,

1255
01:19:18,667 --> 01:19:21,205
more sure of yourself.

1256
01:19:21,333 --> 01:19:25,156
I was so angry with you at first
when you wanted Susan.

1257
01:19:27,250 --> 01:19:30,948
You seemed to want things
for all the wrong reasons.

1258
01:19:31,625 --> 01:19:35,539
And you didn't see how you were
damaging yourself as a person.

1259
01:19:36,542 --> 01:19:40,081
You weren't proud to be you,
just to be yourself.

1260
01:19:41,792 --> 01:19:43,704
But you're proud now, aren't you?

1261
01:19:44,750 --> 01:19:45,750
Oh, yes.

1262
01:19:47,625 --> 01:19:50,743
Right now I'm the proudest man
in the world.

1263
01:19:55,167 --> 01:19:57,784
You've got so much, Joe.

1264
01:19:57,917 --> 01:19:59,658
Everything.

1265
01:19:59,792 --> 01:20:02,375
You don't ever have to pretend.

1266
01:20:02,500 --> 01:20:05,288
You just have to be yourself.

1267
01:20:05,417 --> 01:20:08,865
"This above all:

1268
01:20:09,000 --> 01:20:13,119
"To thine own self be true.

1269
01:20:13,250 --> 01:20:14,866
"And..." And...

1270
01:20:15,000 --> 01:20:16,286
- And?
- I've forgotten the rest.

1271
01:20:16,417 --> 01:20:19,581
"And it must follow,

1272
01:20:19,708 --> 01:20:22,200
"as the night the day.

1273
01:20:22,333 --> 01:20:24,666
- "Thou then canst..."
- "Thou canst not then..."

1274
01:20:24,792 --> 01:20:27,864
"Thou canst not then
be false to any man."

1275
01:20:29,333 --> 01:20:33,077
You're an educated and moral witch, Alice,
and I love you.

1276
01:20:35,292 --> 01:20:37,955
Oh, I've something for you.

1277
01:20:43,708 --> 01:20:45,370
Oh, no, it's much too nice for me.

1278
01:20:45,500 --> 01:20:47,867
I want you to have it.

1279
01:20:49,000 --> 01:20:51,617
To remind you
of the happiness we had.

1280
01:21:00,792 --> 01:21:02,579
You talk like a requiem.

1281
01:21:04,583 --> 01:21:06,950
This is only the beginning.

1282
01:21:08,792 --> 01:21:10,579
Are you sure?

1283
01:21:15,000 --> 01:21:17,413
I can't live without you.

1284
01:21:17,542 --> 01:21:19,374
I've tried and I can't.

1285
01:21:20,625 --> 01:21:22,366
I need you.

1286
01:21:28,375 --> 01:21:30,116
Do you really mean it?

1287
01:21:32,292 --> 01:21:34,784
Do you want me to divorce George?

1288
01:21:34,917 --> 01:21:36,783
Yes.

1289
01:21:36,917 --> 01:21:38,408
But would you?

1290
01:21:41,583 --> 01:21:44,121
- What's so funny?
- You.

1291
01:21:47,708 --> 01:21:49,700
I'm frightened.

1292
01:21:49,833 --> 01:21:53,827
Nobody was ever meant
to be as happy as I am now.

1293
01:21:53,958 --> 01:21:55,745
It can't last.

1294
01:21:55,875 --> 01:21:59,243
It's like... like a bubble
that's going to burst

1295
01:21:59,375 --> 01:22:01,913
when I get on that train tomorrow.

1296
01:22:03,292 --> 01:22:05,579
Mm... That train.

1297
01:22:10,042 --> 01:22:12,284
Change your mind, Joe,
and come with me.

1298
01:22:12,417 --> 01:22:16,331
No, it's best as we arranged.
I'll take the next train

1299
01:22:16,458 --> 01:22:19,292
and see you when I get back
from Dufdon at Elspeth's.

1300
01:22:20,583 --> 01:22:22,495
It's only ten days.

1301
01:22:23,833 --> 01:22:25,449
It's only a lifetime.

1302
01:22:30,792 --> 01:22:34,456
We'll work it out so that we can spend
the rest of our lives together.

1303
01:22:36,458 --> 01:22:38,450
Give me a cigarette, darling.

1304
01:22:40,792 --> 01:22:44,240
I have a feeling
that this is all we're gonna have.

1305
01:22:49,625 --> 01:22:51,787
This is only the beginning.

1306
01:23:04,083 --> 01:23:06,666
Please walk away now, darling.

1307
01:23:06,792 --> 01:23:08,658
Walk away and don't look back.

1308
01:23:12,000 --> 01:23:13,207
Think of me.

1309
01:23:46,500 --> 01:23:47,581
Yes?

1310
01:23:52,750 --> 01:23:55,242
- Mr Aisgill, what can I...?
- Sit down.

1311
01:23:57,333 --> 01:23:59,245
What can I do for you?

1312
01:23:59,375 --> 01:24:01,332
Cigarette?

1313
01:24:01,458 --> 01:24:03,324
Nice case you have there.

1314
01:24:06,667 --> 01:24:08,579
You know why I'm here.

1315
01:24:09,417 --> 01:24:11,750
Alice tells me she wants to divorce me.

1316
01:24:11,875 --> 01:24:13,915
- Well, I'm not agreeable.
- You haven't any choice.

1317
01:24:14,000 --> 01:24:16,868
She's my wife and she's going
to remain my wife.

1318
01:24:17,000 --> 01:24:19,913
I want to make this quite clear to you.
She has no grounds for divorce.

1319
01:24:20,042 --> 01:24:23,410
Everybody knows the way you treat Alice,
about you and your women.

1320
01:24:23,542 --> 01:24:25,249
But nobody can prove anything.

1321
01:24:26,375 --> 01:24:29,618
The difference between you and me
is that I haven't been indiscreet enough

1322
01:24:29,750 --> 01:24:31,707
to leave evidence lying around.

1323
01:24:32,458 --> 01:24:33,949
- Meaning what?
- Just this.

1324
01:24:34,083 --> 01:24:36,166
If she brings an action for divorce,
I'll fight it.

1325
01:24:36,292 --> 01:24:39,285
I'll smear you both across the headlines.

1326
01:24:39,417 --> 01:24:40,749
It will make fine reading.

1327
01:24:40,875 --> 01:24:42,161
Elspeth's flat,

1328
01:24:42,292 --> 01:24:45,330
the naked bathing in Dorset
and all the rest of it.

1329
01:24:45,458 --> 01:24:48,246
- How did you know?
- I make it my business to know.

1330
01:24:48,375 --> 01:24:52,574
It'll break you because you can't stand
a scandal like that, and you know it.

1331
01:24:52,708 --> 01:24:56,201
And you won't get Alice either,
because I still won't let her go.

1332
01:24:57,625 --> 01:24:59,491
You can't hold her.

1333
01:24:59,625 --> 01:25:01,601
Maybe she can't divorce you,
but she can leave you.

1334
01:25:01,625 --> 01:25:04,163
- You can't stop her from leaving you.
- Can you keep her?

1335
01:25:04,292 --> 01:25:06,909
I can keep her
because I love her.

1336
01:25:07,042 --> 01:25:10,206
She's ten years older than you
and she hasn't a penny of her own.

1337
01:25:10,333 --> 01:25:12,620
If she leaves me,
I'll sue you for enticement.

1338
01:25:12,750 --> 01:25:14,662
Then you won't be able
to support even yourself.

1339
01:25:17,375 --> 01:25:20,163
You've got everything
pretty well worked out, haven't you?

1340
01:25:20,875 --> 01:25:22,662
I have. There are no loopholes.

1341
01:25:22,792 --> 01:25:25,034
Get it clear: from now on
you leave Alice alone.

1342
01:25:25,167 --> 01:25:27,284
- Understand me?
- Why won't you let her go? Why?

1343
01:25:27,417 --> 01:25:30,285
Because she's my wife, that's why.

1344
01:25:32,083 --> 01:25:34,120
Are you trying to tell me
you still love her?

1345
01:25:34,250 --> 01:25:36,583
I'm not trying to tell you anything.

1346
01:25:41,208 --> 01:25:43,575
I've let you off lightly.

1347
01:25:43,708 --> 01:25:46,121
There will be no more warnings.

1348
01:25:55,417 --> 01:25:56,417
Say that again.

1349
01:25:56,542 --> 01:26:00,081
June and I have decided to go steady.
I wanted you to be the first one to know.

1350
01:26:00,208 --> 01:26:03,042
- That's just wonderful.
- Oh, Joe, show some enthusiasm.

1351
01:26:03,167 --> 01:26:06,205
Well, I seem to remember
you wanted a girl with no responsibilities

1352
01:26:06,333 --> 01:26:08,791
and a small family business
in the background.

1353
01:26:08,917 --> 01:26:10,704
That don't seem
to matter much anymore.

1354
01:26:11,667 --> 01:26:13,909
Oh, and what about the invalid mother?

1355
01:26:14,042 --> 01:26:15,328
Oh, I get it!

1356
01:26:15,458 --> 01:26:18,121
She's died and left you
a large insurance policy.

1357
01:26:18,250 --> 01:26:19,582
Oh, Joe!

1358
01:26:20,958 --> 01:26:22,824
No, seriously,
what about her invalid mother?

1359
01:26:22,958 --> 01:26:26,247
That don't seem to matter much either.

1360
01:26:26,375 --> 01:26:28,788
June's a fine kid.
You couldn't have done better, Charles.

1361
01:26:28,917 --> 01:26:32,410
As a matter of fact,
I'm thinking of settling down myself.

1362
01:26:33,625 --> 01:26:35,912
That might be June.
I'll be right with you, Joe.

1363
01:26:42,208 --> 01:26:43,494
Hey, Joe.

1364
01:26:43,625 --> 01:26:45,582
It's for you. Mr Brown.

1365
01:26:45,708 --> 01:26:46,915
Who?

1366
01:26:47,042 --> 01:26:48,999
God almighty! Brown, that's who.

1367
01:26:49,125 --> 01:26:50,411
He wants to talk to you.

1368
01:26:50,542 --> 01:26:53,125
Tell him my mother sent me
touring on the Riviera.

1369
01:26:53,250 --> 01:26:55,617
Oh, no, Joe.
Come on, quick. He's waiting.

1370
01:26:55,750 --> 01:26:58,208
- Well, let him wait.
- Joe, what's got into you lately?

1371
01:26:58,333 --> 01:27:01,781
- I've had enough threats for one day.
- Well, come on!

1372
01:27:02,792 --> 01:27:04,909
Oh, all right, I'm coming.

1373
01:27:09,458 --> 01:27:11,290
Yes?

1374
01:27:11,417 --> 01:27:14,910
Are you sure it's me
you want to speak to, Mr Brown?

1375
01:27:15,042 --> 01:27:16,249
Oh...

1376
01:27:19,250 --> 01:27:20,786
Yes, sir.

1377
01:27:30,167 --> 01:27:32,124
What did he want?

1378
01:27:32,250 --> 01:27:35,118
He wants me to lunch with him
at the Conservative Club at one o'clock.

1379
01:28:03,000 --> 01:28:05,367
Sit down. You're late.

1380
01:28:05,500 --> 01:28:07,537
He'll have the game soup.

1381
01:28:09,792 --> 01:28:11,909
It's the first time
you've been in this club, is it?

1382
01:28:12,042 --> 01:28:14,284
This or any other Conservative Club.

1383
01:28:14,417 --> 01:28:17,785
My father would turn in his grave
if he could see me now.

1384
01:28:17,917 --> 01:28:21,536
So would mine,
but we're not bound by our fathers.

1385
01:28:22,625 --> 01:28:25,038
Now, I've got a proposition for you.

1386
01:28:25,167 --> 01:28:26,999
You're a clever young man.

1387
01:28:27,125 --> 01:28:30,243
You don't want to stay in the town hall
the rest of your life, do you?

1388
01:28:30,375 --> 01:28:33,163
Now's the time that accountants
can do well for theirselves.

1389
01:28:34,083 --> 01:28:37,201
Now, I'm willing
to set you up in business,

1390
01:28:37,333 --> 01:28:39,575
buy you a partnership.

1391
01:28:39,708 --> 01:28:41,700
Well, what do you say?

1392
01:28:43,375 --> 01:28:44,786
There's a catch somewhere.

1393
01:28:46,250 --> 01:28:48,287
Not a catch, but a condition.

1394
01:28:49,042 --> 01:28:52,285
I'll set you up on condition
that you never see Susan again

1395
01:28:52,417 --> 01:28:53,783
or communicate with her.

1396
01:28:56,542 --> 01:28:58,955
Now, just what's so funny
about that, young man?

1397
01:29:00,167 --> 01:29:01,749
Nothing I could explain.

1398
01:29:02,208 --> 01:29:04,450
If you agree,
I'll make you a rich man.

1399
01:29:05,292 --> 01:29:09,161
You'll be a damn sight better off
than you'll ever be in local government.

1400
01:29:09,875 --> 01:29:11,537
Well, what do you say?

1401
01:29:14,083 --> 01:29:15,745
Are you trying to buy me off?

1402
01:29:15,875 --> 01:29:17,457
That's right.

1403
01:29:17,583 --> 01:29:21,202
I'm buying you off
and I'm paying a damn fine price for it.

1404
01:29:21,333 --> 01:29:23,040
Come on, now, use your head.

1405
01:29:23,167 --> 01:29:26,660
You want to improve yourself,
you want to get in among the money.

1406
01:29:26,792 --> 01:29:29,159
All right, I don't blame you for that.

1407
01:29:30,250 --> 01:29:32,242
But you're not getting
at my brass through Susan.

1408
01:29:32,375 --> 01:29:35,413
You wouldn't talk to me like that
if I were Jack Wales

1409
01:29:35,542 --> 01:29:37,249
and had a rich daddy behind me.

1410
01:29:37,375 --> 01:29:39,833
I don't give a damn for Jack Wales.

1411
01:29:39,958 --> 01:29:42,792
A nice little business merger
between the two families.

1412
01:29:42,917 --> 01:29:44,499
I don't barter my daughter.

1413
01:29:45,375 --> 01:29:47,492
- You're trying to barter her now.
- That's enough!

1414
01:29:49,000 --> 01:29:52,038
I told you my offer.
It's the best chance you'll ever have.

1415
01:29:52,167 --> 01:29:54,204
Now, take it or leave it,

1416
01:29:54,333 --> 01:29:56,370
but get this into your head:

1417
01:29:57,208 --> 01:30:00,246
if you refuse it,
I'm going to break you.

1418
01:30:01,333 --> 01:30:04,451
And what's more,
I shall run you out of Warnley!

1419
01:30:06,250 --> 01:30:08,708
Everybody wants to run me
out of Warnley.

1420
01:30:12,292 --> 01:30:15,956
Let's say you kick me out
and I take Susan with me.

1421
01:30:17,208 --> 01:30:18,699
She's in love with me, you know?

1422
01:30:18,833 --> 01:30:20,950
Susan's too young
to know her own mind.

1423
01:30:21,083 --> 01:30:22,699
She'll do as I tell her.

1424
01:30:22,833 --> 01:30:25,325
If she disobeys me,
I shall cut her off without a penny.

1425
01:30:26,125 --> 01:30:28,117
You mean throw her out?

1426
01:30:28,250 --> 01:30:29,411
If necessary.

1427
01:30:30,000 --> 01:30:31,866
I thought that might interest you.

1428
01:30:33,958 --> 01:30:35,165
No!

1429
01:30:37,333 --> 01:30:40,167
I say "nah" to your bloody rotten offer!

1430
01:30:40,292 --> 01:30:41,908
Wait a minute!

1431
01:30:48,708 --> 01:30:51,166
Now I'll tell you
what you're going to do.

1432
01:30:54,625 --> 01:30:56,241
Sit down.

1433
01:31:01,708 --> 01:31:05,497
You're marrying her
with my consent, right quick.

1434
01:31:05,625 --> 01:31:07,742
- Am I?
- That's right.

1435
01:31:09,583 --> 01:31:11,791
But I... I don't understand.

1436
01:31:12,292 --> 01:31:15,035
Don't you?
The reason's very simple.

1437
01:31:16,625 --> 01:31:19,117
Yes, I'm glad
you have the grace to blush.

1438
01:31:20,875 --> 01:31:23,242
But... but why didn't she tell me?

1439
01:31:25,083 --> 01:31:28,372
Chicken again?
I'll be turning into one soon.

1440
01:31:28,500 --> 01:31:31,914
- We'll have the pie.
- I'll have a scotch, please, a large one.

1441
01:31:32,042 --> 01:31:33,123
She didn't tell you

1442
01:31:33,250 --> 01:31:35,643
because she didn't want you
to wed her out of her sense of duty.

1443
01:31:35,667 --> 01:31:37,829
And I didn't tell you
because I wanted to try you out.

1444
01:31:38,583 --> 01:31:41,291
- Hmm.
- No need to laugh like that, young man.

1445
01:31:42,042 --> 01:31:45,114
This isn't the way I planned
to have my daughter wed.

1446
01:31:45,250 --> 01:31:48,698
Now, listen, you're gonna throw up
your job at the town hall.

1447
01:31:49,542 --> 01:31:51,374
I need somebody
to reorganise the office.

1448
01:31:51,500 --> 01:31:54,493
I want some efficiency
in that side of the business.

1449
01:32:00,708 --> 01:32:01,708
Well?

1450
01:32:22,208 --> 01:32:23,289
How about salary?

1451
01:32:27,000 --> 01:32:28,491
Thousand a year to start with.

1452
01:32:29,167 --> 01:32:30,908
Nought if you don't make a success of it.

1453
01:32:32,083 --> 01:32:34,575
And there's just one other matter
to be cleared up.

1454
01:32:34,708 --> 01:32:36,199
If you don't, it's all off.

1455
01:32:36,750 --> 01:32:39,367
You've been too ruddy long
about it already.

1456
01:32:40,458 --> 01:32:43,201
Leave off Alice Aisgill.

1457
01:32:43,333 --> 01:32:44,540
Now!

1458
01:32:45,042 --> 01:32:47,284
I'm not gonna have my daughter
hurt anymore,

1459
01:32:47,417 --> 01:32:50,489
and I'm not gonna have my son-in-law
in the divorce courts either.

1460
01:32:50,625 --> 01:32:52,241
Not on account
of an old whore like that.

1461
01:32:55,625 --> 01:32:57,662
There's no need
to talk about her in that way.

1462
01:32:57,792 --> 01:33:00,330
I use words that fit.

1463
01:33:00,458 --> 01:33:04,156
Now, get done with her.
I'll not have it put off anymore.

1464
01:33:05,208 --> 01:33:07,621
Bring coffee for two.

1465
01:33:07,750 --> 01:33:09,082
I'm driving over to Leddersford.

1466
01:33:09,208 --> 01:33:12,076
I'll drop you off at the house,
Susan wants to talk to you.

1467
01:33:12,208 --> 01:33:14,200
But... I've got to get back
to the office.

1468
01:33:14,333 --> 01:33:17,201
I told Hoylake you were taking
the afternoon off.

1469
01:33:19,833 --> 01:33:22,291
You can fix just about anything,
can't you?

1470
01:33:22,958 --> 01:33:24,324
Just about.

1471
01:33:44,250 --> 01:33:46,708
I'll tell Miss Susan you're here.

1472
01:34:10,292 --> 01:34:11,373
Joe!

1473
01:34:20,708 --> 01:34:22,950
Joe, isn't it wonderful?

1474
01:34:23,083 --> 01:34:24,790
I'm so happy.

1475
01:34:25,583 --> 01:34:27,791
Now we're really going to be married.

1476
01:34:29,083 --> 01:34:31,291
Why didn't you tell me
about the baby?

1477
01:34:32,208 --> 01:34:36,373
Oh, I don't know,
you've seemed so strange lately,

1478
01:34:36,500 --> 01:34:38,537
as if you didn't like me very much.

1479
01:34:39,583 --> 01:34:41,415
But it's all right now, isn't it, Joe?

1480
01:34:41,542 --> 01:34:43,283
Yes.

1481
01:34:43,417 --> 01:34:45,625
Yes, it's all all right now.

1482
01:34:51,958 --> 01:34:53,039
Joe?

1483
01:34:55,875 --> 01:34:59,539
People have told me,
even Daddy said that you were...

1484
01:35:00,667 --> 01:35:03,205
that you were having an affair
with Alice Aisgill.

1485
01:35:05,542 --> 01:35:07,033
How could you?

1486
01:35:07,167 --> 01:35:09,250
She's so... old!

1487
01:35:11,542 --> 01:35:15,411
Just an old whore like her?
That's what you mean, isn't it?

1488
01:35:15,542 --> 01:35:17,408
Well, it's all over now,

1489
01:35:17,542 --> 01:35:19,078
so just forget about it.

1490
01:35:19,208 --> 01:35:21,700
- How do I know that?
- Because I'm telling you.

1491
01:35:21,833 --> 01:35:23,244
Listen, Joe,

1492
01:35:23,375 --> 01:35:26,334
if you so much as look at her again,
we're through.

1493
01:35:26,458 --> 01:35:28,745
I don't care about the baby
or anything. I mean it.

1494
01:35:28,875 --> 01:35:30,582
I won't be second best!

1495
01:35:30,708 --> 01:35:32,415
Promise me
you'll never ever see her again.

1496
01:35:32,542 --> 01:35:33,874
I can't do that.

1497
01:35:35,667 --> 01:35:39,456
I'm going to see her just one more time
and tell her about us.

1498
01:35:39,583 --> 01:35:42,326
- You could write to her.
- I'm going to see her!

1499
01:35:48,500 --> 01:35:49,581
Joe...

1500
01:35:51,458 --> 01:35:53,450
You do love me, don't you?

1501
01:35:56,833 --> 01:35:59,951
May I come in?
Oh, hello, Mr Lampton.

1502
01:36:00,083 --> 01:36:03,451
I suppose now I'd better call you Joe.

1503
01:36:03,583 --> 01:36:07,031
Well, the sooner we get on
with the arrangements, the better.

1504
01:36:07,167 --> 01:36:11,161
We've decided on a white wedding
in spite of the circumstances.

1505
01:36:11,292 --> 01:36:14,660
The first thing I'll require from you
is a list of the guests.

1506
01:36:35,958 --> 01:36:38,792
Darling, I thought you'd never come.
You're so late.

1507
01:36:38,917 --> 01:36:40,533
Come on.

1508
01:36:43,542 --> 01:36:45,158
I've got a surprise for you.

1509
01:36:46,000 --> 01:36:47,787
Come on, open it.

1510
01:36:47,917 --> 01:36:48,998
Oh...

1511
01:36:53,042 --> 01:36:54,499
Don't like it?

1512
01:36:55,125 --> 01:36:56,616
Yes, I... I like it very much, but...

1513
01:36:56,750 --> 01:36:59,242
If you don't like it,
you can change it for another colour.

1514
01:37:00,500 --> 01:37:02,662
What's wrong?
You look so serious.

1515
01:37:02,792 --> 01:37:04,909
No, I... I like the colour.

1516
01:37:05,750 --> 01:37:06,831
Alice...

1517
01:37:07,750 --> 01:37:09,412
Alice, sit down.

1518
01:37:09,542 --> 01:37:11,625
You won't be hurting my feelings.

1519
01:37:11,750 --> 01:37:14,163
I'm not touchy about things like that.

1520
01:37:22,125 --> 01:37:23,457
I'm going to marry Susan.

1521
01:37:25,958 --> 01:37:28,951
Everything's fixed, even the date.

1522
01:37:32,292 --> 01:37:34,033
I'm going to marry her.

1523
01:37:42,375 --> 01:37:44,492
I've put her in the family way.

1524
01:37:48,292 --> 01:37:50,909
Well, what did you expect me to do?
Run away?

1525
01:37:54,750 --> 01:37:58,664
No, but that doesn't mean
you have to marry her.

1526
01:37:58,792 --> 01:38:00,704
I've got to marry her!

1527
01:38:00,833 --> 01:38:04,702
- You'll be telling me next you love her.
- Look, Alice, please.

1528
01:38:04,833 --> 01:38:07,041
Please don't let's have a scene.

1529
01:38:08,708 --> 01:38:10,574
We were loving friends, remember?

1530
01:38:10,708 --> 01:38:14,748
Right from the start you said
we were only loving friends.

1531
01:38:18,792 --> 01:38:22,365
It wasn't possible anyway, you and me.
You know it wasn't.

1532
01:38:22,500 --> 01:38:24,366
Well, George wouldn't let you go.

1533
01:38:24,500 --> 01:38:27,018
If you'd have taken him to court,
he'd have thrown more muck at us

1534
01:38:27,042 --> 01:38:28,533
than either of us could stand.

1535
01:38:29,042 --> 01:38:31,159
I would have lost my job.

1536
01:38:31,292 --> 01:38:32,999
What could we have lived on?

1537
01:38:40,583 --> 01:38:43,906
You're a timid soul, aren't you?

1538
01:38:47,208 --> 01:38:50,167
I suppose you are going
to work for Brown.

1539
01:38:53,708 --> 01:38:54,744
Yes.

1540
01:38:58,125 --> 01:39:00,583
You've done very well
for yourself, Joe.

1541
01:39:01,708 --> 01:39:05,156
Finally, you've got
everything you wanted.

1542
01:39:06,083 --> 01:39:07,199
Haven't you?

1543
01:39:15,167 --> 01:39:18,615
There is something
you have never understood, Joe.

1544
01:39:18,750 --> 01:39:20,912
These people at the top,

1545
01:39:21,042 --> 01:39:22,999
they are the same as anybody else.

1546
01:39:23,667 --> 01:39:27,911
But you had it inside of you
to be so much bigger than any of them.

1547
01:39:29,375 --> 01:39:31,913
You just had to be yourself.

1548
01:39:33,208 --> 01:39:34,995
That was all.

1549
01:39:36,792 --> 01:39:39,034
With me you were yourself.

1550
01:39:40,292 --> 01:39:41,783
Only with me.

1551
01:39:43,750 --> 01:39:45,742
Don't you understand
what you've done?

1552
01:39:47,250 --> 01:39:48,866
Look, Alice...

1553
01:39:51,792 --> 01:39:53,624
I'm going to marry Susan.

1554
01:39:54,667 --> 01:39:57,080
All right, maybe I do love you,

1555
01:39:57,208 --> 01:39:58,665
but I'm going to marry her.

1556
01:39:58,792 --> 01:40:01,409
Now, please don't make it
any more difficult for us both.

1557
01:40:01,542 --> 01:40:03,158
Oh, to hell with you!

1558
01:40:04,250 --> 01:40:07,869
Do you think our love
is just like a layer of dirt?

1559
01:40:08,000 --> 01:40:09,787
