- She's had a skinful.
- I've never seen her like that before.

1581
01:42:53,208 --> 01:42:56,042
She'll be all right.
She knows her way around.

1582
01:43:46,625 --> 01:43:47,911
Good morning.

1583
01:43:48,042 --> 01:43:50,455
- Good morning.
- Good morning, Mr Lampton.

1584
01:43:50,583 --> 01:43:52,119
Oh, Miss Beth?

1585
01:43:52,250 --> 01:43:55,038
I'd like to get everything outstanding
settled as soon as possible,

1586
01:43:55,167 --> 01:43:56,248
starting with the gas.

1587
01:43:56,375 --> 01:43:58,415
How about the profit and loss
appropriation account?

1588
01:43:58,542 --> 01:43:59,703
Oh, it can wait.

1589
01:43:59,833 --> 01:44:03,076
Mr Lampton, I would like
to congratulate you.

1590
01:44:03,208 --> 01:44:05,074
Mr Hoylake told Gladys and...

1591
01:44:05,208 --> 01:44:07,370
Well, you know
how these things get about.

1592
01:44:07,500 --> 01:44:10,459
- I hope you'll be very happy together.
- Thank you very much.

1593
01:44:10,583 --> 01:44:13,826
- Did you hear about the accident?
- Have you set the date of the wedding?

1594
01:44:13,958 --> 01:44:16,120
- No, not definitely.
- Alice Aisgill. She's dead.

1595
01:44:16,250 --> 01:44:18,242
It will be the wedding of the year,
I'm sure.

1596
01:44:18,375 --> 01:44:20,162
- Who's dead?
- Alice Aisgill.

1597
01:44:20,292 --> 01:44:21,749
- I hope so.
- And Miss Brown,

1598
01:44:21,875 --> 01:44:24,115
if you don't mind my saying so,
will make a lovely bride.

1599
01:44:24,167 --> 01:44:26,284
She ran her car
into the cliff at Sparrow Hill.

1600
01:44:26,417 --> 01:44:27,874
Heard she was drunk.

1601
01:44:28,000 --> 01:44:29,036
