1602
01:44:29,167 --> 01:44:31,033
Alice Aisgill, Mr Lampton.

1603
01:44:31,167 --> 01:44:34,706
They say that the car was bent like that
and blood all over the place.

1604
01:44:34,833 --> 01:44:36,745
What was she doing
up on Sparrow Hill anyway?

1605
01:44:36,875 --> 01:44:39,208
Oh, goodness knows.
She'd been drinking all right.

1606
01:44:39,333 --> 01:44:41,416
Probably didn't know where she was.

1607
01:44:41,542 --> 01:44:42,908
- There he is!
- Joe!

1608
01:44:43,042 --> 01:44:45,580
Congratulations, lad. It couldn't
have happened to a nicer chap.

1609
01:44:45,708 --> 01:44:47,976
He was trying to tell me the other night.
Weren't you, Joe?

1610
01:44:48,000 --> 01:44:50,868
Come on, bring that through now.
We've got a surprise for you, Joe.

1611
01:44:51,000 --> 01:44:52,662
Come on, lad, quick!

1612
01:44:52,792 --> 01:44:54,704
Well, unwrap it!

1613
