01:49:56,500 --> 01:50:00,414
Now, you turn left, remember,
and go straight on down the canal.

1692
01:50:03,000 --> 01:50:05,117
Have you enough for a taxi?

1693
01:50:06,083 --> 01:50:07,699
Oh, God, they've woken up.

1694
01:50:09,167 --> 01:50:10,749
Good night, Jack.

1695
01:50:10,875 --> 01:50:12,491
It's been lovely.

1696
01:50:13,000 --> 01:50:14,616
Really it has.

1697
01:51:30,542 --> 01:51:31,578
That's enough.

1698
01:52:48,042 --> 01:52:49,908
Joe! Joe!

1699
01:53:04,125 --> 01:53:06,117
Time to come home, Joe.

1700
01:53:09,000 --> 01:53:11,208
It's all right, love.

1701
01:53:11,333 --> 01:53:13,370
Everything's all right now.

1702
01:53:17,458 --> 01:53:18,494
I've...

1703
01:53:20,750 --> 01:53:23,993
- ...murdered her.
- Oh, shush!

1704
01:53:24,125 --> 01:53:25,912
I've killed her.

1705
01:53:27,208 --> 01:53:30,167
- Everybody knows I've killed her.
- Don't take on so.

1706
01:53:30,292 --> 01:53:32,875
I wasn't there, but I killed her.

1707
01:53:34,125 --> 01:53:35,912
Nobody's blaming you, Joe.

1708
01:53:36,542 --> 01:53:39,865
You don't see it now,
but she'd have ruined your whole life.

1709
01:53:40,667 --> 01:53:43,580
Oh, no, nobody will ever blame you, Joe.

1710
01:53:48,208 --> 01:53:50,541
Nobody but... me.

1711
01:53:54,625 --> 01:53:56,708
That's the trouble.

1712
01:54:09,750 --> 01:54:12,618
I require and charge you both,

1713
01:54:12,750 --> 01:54:16,664
as ye will answer
at the dreadful Day of Judgement

1714
01:54:16,792 --> 01:54:20,832
when the secrets of all hearts
shall be disclosed,

1715
01:54:20,958 --> 01:54:23,701
that if either of you know any impediment

1716
01:54:23,833 --> 01:54:27,782
why ye may not be lawfully
joined together in matrimony,

1717
01:54:27,917 --> 01:54:29,749
ye do now confess it,

1718
01:54:30,667 --> 01:54:32,533
for be ye well assured

1719
01:54:32,667 --> 01:54:37,332
that so many as are coupled together
otherwise than God's words doth allow

1720
01:54:37,458 --> 01:54:39,950
are not joined together by God,

1721
01:54:40,083 --> 01:54:42,621
neither is their matrimony lawful.

1722
01:54:44,042 --> 01:54:45,328
Joseph,

1723
01:54:46,458 --> 01:54:49,292
wilt thou have this woman
to thy wedded wife,

1724
01:54:50,333 --> 01:54:53,405
to live together after God's ordinance

1725
01:54:53,542 --> 01:54:55,704
in the holy estate of matrimony?

1726
01:54:56,667 --> 01:55:01,992
Wilt thou love her, comfort her,
honour and keep her

1727
01:55:03,000 --> 01:55:05,367
in sickness and in health

1728
01:55:06,375 --> 01:55:08,708
and, forsaking all other,

1729
01:55:09,583 --> 01:55:11,996
keep thee only unto her

1730
01:55:12,833 --> 01:55:15,291
so long as ye both shall live?

1731
01:55:25,958 --> 01:55:26,994
I will.

1732
01:55:42,583 --> 01:55:44,495
Good luck, Joe.

1733
01:56:13,500 --> 01:56:18,746
Joe, wasn't it absolutely
the most wonderful wedding?

1734
01:56:22,375 --> 01:56:25,413
Now we really belong to each other,

1735
01:56:25,542 --> 01:56:27,158
"till death us do part".

1736
01:56:32,458 --> 01:56:34,370
Darling, you're crying.

1737
01:56:35,083 --> 01:56:38,281
I believe you really are
sentimental after all.
